<subSubSection id="C309EEC62F6EFFE54EAFF95DFF36F8EE" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6EFFE54EAFF95DFF36F8EE" blockId="20.[151,1437,1725,2002]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54EAFF95DFD91F956" bold="true" box="[199,590,1761,1786]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Pertinent taxonomic references.</emphasis>
Ruibal (1952), Uzzell &amp; Barry (1971), Hoogmoed (1973), Ávila-Pires (1995), Pellegrino 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54F03F8BBFE7BF8B2" box="[363,420,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">et al.</emphasis>
(1999, 2011), Rodrigues &amp; Ávila-Pires (2005), Rodrigues 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54A56F8BBFBAFF8B2" box="[1086,1136,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">et al</emphasis>
. (2013), Goicoechea 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54B0BF8BBFA4AF8B2" box="[1379,1429,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">et al</emphasis>
. (2016).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C309EEC62F6EFFE44EAFF8F1FAD0FF78" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="172" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6EFFE44EAFF8F1FAD0FF78" blockId="20.[151,1437,1725,2002]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="172" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54EAFF8F1FE2FF8CA" bold="true" box="[199,496,1869,1894]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6EFFE54F9EF8F1FD33F8CA" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[502,748,1869,1894]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guianense">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54F9EF8F1FD33F8CA" box="[502,748,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Loxopholis guianense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to eastern 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6EFFE54D8BF8F1FB86F8CA" box="[995,1113,1869,1894]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="20" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
, with its western distribution delimited by the 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6EFFE54F0EF8CDFE06F826" box="[358,473,1905,1930]" name="Guyana" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Essequibo</collectingCountry>
and Trombetas rivers north of the Amazon River, and Xingu River south of it, occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6EFFE54F45F829FEABF802" box="[301,372,1941,1966]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6EFFE54FEBF829FDEFF802" box="[387,560,1941,1966]" country="France" name="Guyane" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6EFFE54FEBF829FDEFF802" box="[387,560,1941,1966]" name="French Guiana" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6EFFE54C56F829FD73F802" box="[574,684,1941,1966]" name="Suriname" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Suriname</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6EFFE54C86F82AFC9AF802" box="[750,837,1942,1966]" name="Guyana" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Guyana</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="1328A1C82F6EFFE54D30F829FC71F802" box="[856,942,1941,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1535,1557]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,277,1504]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,267,1513]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distribution of examined material of Loxopholis guianense, L. osvaldoi, L. snethlageae, and Micrablepharus atticolus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581988/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6EFFE54D81F829FBEFF802" box="[1001,1072,1941,1966]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6EFFE54EFFF806FF34F87E" box="[151,235,1978,2002]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Amapá</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6EFFE54E92F806FEF0F87E" box="[250,303,1978,2002]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Pará</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6EFFE54F19F806FE34F87E" box="[369,491,1978,2002]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6EFFE54F91F805FD2DF87E" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[505,754,1977,2002]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guianense">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54F91F805FD2DF87E" box="[505,754,1977,2002]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Loxopholis guianense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits primary terra firme and flooded (varzea) forests, where it is found among the leaf litter, in shaded spots, mostly near creeks (Hoogmoed 1973; Gasc 1986; Hoogmoed &amp; Ávila-Pires 1991; Ribeiro-Júnior 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6FFFE44D13FF01FC6CFF79" box="[891,947,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">et al.</emphasis>
2006; Ávila-Pires 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6FFFE44AEFFF01FB1FFF79" box="[1159,1216,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">et al.</emphasis>
2010).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
